The paper deals with the characterization of languages defined by constraints on the number of occurrences of subwords in a given word. This is a topic that is studied in formal language theory, which falls under the category of cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also uses graph-structural characterization, which is a technique used in algorithms and data structures, falling under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with decidability, which is a topic studied in logic and computability, falling under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity theory, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper also uses information theory, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
